Interview Definition
Record is a special immutable class introduced in Java to reduce boilerplate code for storing data objects.
It automatically generates constructor, getters, equals, hashCode, and toString methods.


Record Class Example
record Employee(int id, String name) {

}
That’s it ✅

Java automatically creates:
Constructor
Getter methods
toString()
equals()
hashCode()

| Class                 | Record                  |
| --------------------- | ----------------------- |
| More boilerplate code | Very less code          |
| Mutable               | Immutable               |
| Need manual methods   | Auto-generated methods  |
| Flexible              | Mainly for data holding |
